@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{isearch-extras.el} extends Emacs' built-in incremental search facility (@samp{isearch}). While isearch is one of the most frequently used Emacs features, its default command set lacks several useful actions: exiting at the other end of the match, copying the match to the kill ring, yanking text literally, and escalating a search to broader scopes.

This package provides two groups of extensions:

@itemize
@item
Commands for use during an active isearch session, bound in @code{isearch-mode-map}, that add new actions at the point of the match (@ref{Match actions}) or transfer the search to another tool (@ref{Search escalation}).
@item
An advice function that uses the active region as the initial search string when starting isearch (@ref{Region as initial input}).
@end itemize

