@node Region as initial input
@section Region as initial input

@findex isearch-extras-use-selection
The function @code{isearch-extras-use-selection} is designed to be added as @samp{:around} advice on @code{isearch-forward} and @code{isearch-backward}. When a region is active at the time isearch is invoked, this function takes the selected text, adds it to the isearch ring, deactivates the mark, and then starts the search with an immediate repeat in the appropriate direction. The effect is that the selected text becomes the search string and point moves to the next (or previous) occurrence.

When no region is active, the function delegates to the original isearch command with no changes.

This provides a quick workflow: select a word or phrase, press @samp{C-s}, and immediately jump to the next occurrence without any additional input.

